<h1><strong>Quick points</strong></h1>
<ul>
<li><strong>fluctuations in baseline that are irregular in amplitude and frequency.</strong></li>
<li><strong>visually quantified as amplitude from peak-to-trough in bpm.</strong></li>
<li><strong>absent: undetectable change in amplitude.</strong></li>
<li><strong>minimal: amplitude range &le; 5 bpm.</strong></li>
<li><strong>moderate: amplitude range 6-25 bpm.</strong></li>
<li><strong>marked: amplitude range &gt; 25 bpm</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><strong>Details</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Determined in 10 minute window, excluding accels and decels.</strong></li>
<li><strong>No distinction is made between short-term variability ('beat-to-beat') and long-term variability, because in </strong><strong>actual practice they are visually determined as a unit.</strong></li>
</ul>